00:23:16,274 --> 00:23:16,874
and it was not fun.

551
00:23:18,775 --> 00:23:19,256
So yeah, that's it.

552
00:23:19,396 --> 00:23:19,716
You're done.

553
00:23:20,497 --> 00:23:21,297
You're done with the event.

554
00:23:22,378 --> 00:23:23,219
Now it's the best part.

555
00:23:23,239 --> 00:23:24,860
You get to check out the sales spike,

556
00:23:24,900 --> 00:23:27,482
because you went to an event and you got a shit ton of sales.

557
00:23:28,622 --> 00:23:31,084
except you didn't because it doesn't work like that.

558
00:23:31,164 --> 00:23:34,126
And that's a huge misconception that developers have.

559
00:23:34,786 --> 00:23:36,828
And in order to represent this, I

560
00:23:36,868 --> 00:23:38,389
went to some developer friends.

561
00:23:38,949 --> 00:23:44,533
And I asked them about their sales graphs.

562
00:23:44,553 --> 00:23:45,493
And here's an example.

