00:24:28,852 --> 00:24:32,013
I went to an event, and then in my hotel,

581
00:24:32,313 --> 00:24:34,873
I ran into James Portnow from Extra Credits.

582
00:24:35,314 --> 00:24:38,154
And then some time passed, and he introduced me

583
00:24:38,274 --> 00:24:40,594
to a publisher that I ended up talking with.

584
00:24:41,755 --> 00:24:42,615
Here's another example.

585
00:24:43,235 --> 00:24:46,095
I went to an event, and then I made a very cool Chinese

586
00:24:46,115 --> 00:24:46,555
developer.

587
00:24:46,996 --> 00:24:49,016
And then some time passed, and he helped

588
00:24:49,056 --> 00:24:51,236
me localize my game in Chinese.

589
00:24:53,097 --> 00:24:56,278
I went to an event, and I met a cool dude sitting

590
00:24:56,338 --> 00:24:59,639
on the couch of the hotel lobby.

591
00:25:00,119 --> 00:25:01,880
And it turns out that he was a director

592
00:25:01,980 --> 00:25:04,321
for a very cool documentary called Game Loading.

593
00:25:04,801 --> 00:25:07,703
Some time passed, and he ended up visiting me in Romania

594
00:25:08,143 --> 00:25:10,744
so he can record a special segment for his documentary.

595
00:25:11,824 --> 00:25:12,805
And I can keep doing this.

596
00:25:12,885 --> 00:25:15,406
I met Northern Lion at an event, and he played my game.

597
00:25:15,446 --> 00:25:17,907
And then some time passed, and he made a video about my game.

598
00:25:18,848 --> 00:25:20,288
And it's the same with Giant Bomb.

599
00:25:20,388 --> 00:25:22,249
They mentioned us on their panel because we

600
00:25:22,289 --> 00:25:23,590
ran into them at an event.

601
00:25:24,250 --> 00:25:26,231
So with all these things in mind,

602
00:25:26,251 --> 00:25:29,813
I want to repeat that events won't get you sales.

603
00:25:30,433 --> 00:25:32,174
They'll get you awesome relationships.

604
00:25:32,874 --> 00:25:35,615
So with that in mind, get ready for the next event.

605
00:25:36,496 --> 00:25:36,756
Thank you.

